list_variables.description: HTTP methods that CloudFront processes and forwards to your Amazon S3 bucket or your                   custom origin. You can specify ["HEAD", "GET"], ["GET", "HEAD",                      "OPTIONS"], or ["DELETE", "GET", "HEAD", "OPTIONS", "PATCH",                      "POST", "PUT"]. If you don't specify a value, AWS CloudFormation specifies                      ["HEAD", "GET"].
list_variables.name: AllowedMethods

list_variables.description: HTTP methods for which CloudFront caches responses. You can specify ["HEAD",                      "GET"] or ["GET", "HEAD", "OPTIONS"]. If you don't specify                   a value, AWS CloudFormation specifies ["HEAD", "GET"].
list_variables.name: CachedMethods

list_variables.description: A list of AWS accounts that can create signed URLs in order to access private                   content.
list_variables.name: TrustedSigners

variables.description: Specifies how CloudFront handles query strings or cookies.
variables.name: ForwardedValues

variables.description: The minimum amount of time that you want objects to stay in the cache before                   CloudFront queries your origin to see whether the object has been updated.
variables.name: MinTTL

variables.description: Indicates whether to use the origin that is associated with this cache behavior                   to distribute media files in the Microsoft Smooth Streaming format.
variables.name: SmoothStreaming

variables.description: The value of ID for the origin that CloudFront routes requests to when the default                   cache behavior is applied to a request.
variables.name: TargetOriginId

variables.description: The protocol that users can use to access the files in the origin that you                   specified in the TargetOriginId property when the default cache                   behavior is applied to a request.
variables.name: ViewerProtocolPolicy
